label.value: regulation of mesenchymal stem cell proliferation involved in nephron morphogenesis

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of mesenchymal stem cell proliferation and contributes to the shaping of a nephron.

label.value: stem cell proliferation

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of stem cells, resulting in the expansion of a stem cell population. A stem cell is a cell that retains the ability to divide and proliferate throughout life to provide progenitor cells that can differentiate into specialized cells.

label.value: mesenchymal stem cell proliferation involved in nephron morphogenesis

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of mesenchymal stem cells, resulting in the expansion of a stem cell population, that contributes to the shaping of a nephron.

label.value: regulation of stem cell proliferation

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of stem cell proliferation. A stem cell is a cell that retains the ability to divide and proliferate throughout life to provide progenitor cells that can differentiate into specialized cells.

label.value: glomerular mesangial cell proliferation

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of glomerular mesangial cells, resulting in the expansion of the population.

label.value: cell proliferation involved in kidney development

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of the population in the kidney.

label.value: extraglomerular mesangial cell proliferation

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of extraglomerular glomerular mesangium cells by cell division, resulting in the expansion of their population. Extraglomerular mesangial cells (also known as lacis cells, Goormaghtigh cells) are light-staining cells in the kidney found outside the glomerulus, near the vascular pole and macula densa.

label.value: intraglomerular mesangial cell proliferation

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of intraglomerular glomerular mesangium cells by cell division, resulting in the expansion of their population. Intraglomerular mesangial cells are specialized pericytes located among the glomerular capillaries within a renal corpuscle of a kidney. They are required for filtration, structural support and phagocytosis.

label.value: regulation of glomerular mesangial cell proliferation

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of glomerular mesangial cell proliferation.

label.value: negative regulation of glomerular mesangial cell proliferation

definition.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of glomerular mesangial cell proliferation.

label.value: positive regulation of glomerular mesangial cell proliferation

definition.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of glomerular mesangial cell proliferation.

label.value: kidney mesenchymal cell proliferation

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of a mesenchymal cell population in the kidney.

label.value: metanephric mesenchymal cell proliferation involved in metanephros development

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of a metanephric mesenchymal cell population.

label.value: condensed mesenchymal cell proliferation

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of a condensed mesenchymal cell population. A condensed mesenchymal cell population is a population of adherent mesenchymal cells.

label.value: mesenchymal cell proliferation involved in ureteric bud development

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of a mesenchymal cell population of the ureteric bud, that contributes to ureteric bud development.

label.value: mesenchymal cell proliferation involved in ureter development

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of a mesenchymal cell population of the ureter, that contributes to ureter development.

label.value: regulation of mesenchymal cell proliferation involved in ureter development

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of mesenchymal cell proliferation that contributes to the progression of the ureter gland over time. A mesenchymal cell is a cell that normally gives rise to other cells that are organized as three-dimensional masses, rather than sheets.

label.value: negative regulation of mesenchymal cell proliferation involved in ureter development

definition.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of mesenchymal cell proliferation that contributes to the progression of the ureter gland over time. A mesenchymal cell is a cell that normally gives rise to other cells that are organized as three-dimensional masses, rather than sheets.

label.value: negative regulation of mesenchymal cell proliferation

definition.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of mesenchymal cell proliferation. A mesenchymal cell is a cell that normally gives rise to other cells that are organized as three-dimensional masses, rather than sheets.

label.value: cell proliferation involved in metanephros development

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of the population in the metanephros.

label.value: metanephric extraglomerular mesangial cell proliferation involved in metanephros development

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of extraglomerular glomerular mesangium cells in the metanephros by cell division, resulting in the expansion of their population. Extraglomerular mesangial cells (also known as lacis cells, Goormaghtigh cells) are light-staining cells in the kidney found outside the glomerulus, near the vascular pole and macula densa.

label.value: metanephric glomerular mesangial cell proliferation involved in metanephros development

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of glomerular mesangial cells in the metanephros, resulting in the expansion of the population.

label.value: metanephric intraglomerular mesangial cell proliferation

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of intraglomerular glomerular mesangium cells in the metanephros by cell division, resulting in the expansion of their population. Intraglomerular mesangial cells are specialized pericytes located among the glomerular capillaries within a renal corpuscle of a kidney. They are required for filtration, structural support and phagocytosis.

label.value: regulation of metanephric glomerular mesangial cell proliferation

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of metanephric glomerular mesangial cell proliferation.

label.value: negative regulation of metanephric glomerular mesangial cell proliferation

definition.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of metanephric glomerular mesangial cell proliferation.

label.value: positive regulation of glomerular metanephric mesangial cell proliferation

definition.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of metanephric glomerular mesangial cell proliferation.

label.value: alpha-glucan catabolic process involved in ascospore release from ascus

definition.value: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of alpha-glucans in the ascus wall that contributes to the release of ascospores from the ascus.

label.value: glucan endo-1,3-beta-D-glucosidase activity involved in ascospore release from ascus

definition.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of 1,3-beta-D-glucosidic linkages in 1,3-beta-D-glucans that contributes to the release of ascospores from the ascus.

label.value: volume-sensitive chloride channel activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the transmembrane transfer of a chloride ion by a volume-sensitive channel. A volume-sensitive channel is a channel that responds to changes in the volume of a cell.

label.value: ascus epiplasm

definition.value: Ascus cytoplasm that is not packaged into ascospores.

label.value: alkene binding

definition.value: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with an alkene, any acyclic branched or unbranched hydrocarbon having one carbon-carbon double bond and the general formula CnH2n.

label.value: modified amino acid binding

definition.value: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a modified amino acid.

label.value: pancreatic stellate cell proliferation

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of pancreatic stellate cells, resulting in the expansion of a pancreatic stellate cell population. Pancreatic stellate cells are found in the periacinar space of the exocrine pancreas and in perivascular and periductal regions of the pancreas, and have long cytoplasmic processes that encircle the base of the acinus.

label.value: NAADP-sensitive calcium-release channel activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the transmembrane transfer of a calcium ion by a channel that opens when nicotinic acid adenine dinucleotide phosphate (NAADP) has been bound by the channel complex or one of its constituent parts.

label.value: cADPR-sensitive calcium-release channel activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the transmembrane transfer of a calcium ion by a channel that opens when cyclic adenosine diphosphate ribose (cADPR) has been bound by the channel complex or one of its constituent parts.

label.value: modified amino acid transmembrane transporter activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of modified amino acids from one side of a membrane to the other.

label.value: histone kinase activity (H3-T3 specific)

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphate group to the threonine-3 residue of the N-terminal tail of histone H3.

label.value: PTW|PP1 phosphatase complex

definition.value: A protein serine|threonine phosphatase complex that contains a catalytic subunit (PPP1CA, PPP1CB or PPP1CC) and the regulatory subunits PPP1R10 (PNUTS), TOX4 and WDR82, and plays a role in the control of chromatin structure and cell cycle progression during the transition from mitosis into interphase.

label.value: histone kinase activity (H2A-S121 specific)

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphate group to the serine-121 residue of the N-terminal tail of histone H2A.

label.value: primary cilium

definition.value: A cilium found on many different cell types that is typically present in a single copy per cell. A primary cilium may have a variable array of axonemal microtubules and may or may not contain molecular motors.

label.value: alpha-carotene epsilon hydroxylase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  alpha-carotene + NADPH + O2 + H+ -eq- alpha-cryptoxanthin + NADP+ + H2O.

label.value: carotene epsilon hydroxylase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  a carotene + NADPH + O2 + H+ -eq- a beta-ring hydroxylcarotene + NADP+ + H2O. Adds a hydroxyl group to the epsilon ring of the alpha-carotene.

label.value: ER membrane insertion complex

definition.value: A protein complex that is involved in the post-translational delivery of tail-anchored (TA) membrane proteins to the endoplasmic reticulum. TA membrane proteins, also called type II transmembrane proteins, contain a single C-terminal transmembrane region. Some ER membrane insertion complex subunits are conserved between different species such as mammals and budding yeast.

label.value: TRC complex

definition.value: An ER membrane insertion complex that contains subunits that recognize two types of transmembrane domain signals. In budding yeast the complex contains Get4p, Get5p, Sgt2p, and at least two heat shock proteins (HSPs).

label.value: detection of stimulus involved in cell cycle checkpoint

definition.value: The series of events in which information about a biological process or quality is received and converted into a molecular signal, contributing to a cell cycle checkpoint.

label.value: signal transduction involved in cell cycle checkpoint

definition.value: A signal transduction process that contributes to a cell cycle checkpoint.

label.value: detection of stimulus involved in cytokinesis checkpoint

definition.value: The series of events in which information about the formation and integrity of cytokinetic structures, such as the contractile ring, is received and converted into a molecular signal, contributing to a cytokinesis checkpoint.

label.value: signal transduction involved in cytokinesis checkpoint

definition.value: A signal transduction process that contributes to a cytokinesis checkpoint.

label.value: detection of stimulus involved in DNA integrity checkpoint

definition.value: The series of events in which information about DNA integrity is received and converted into a molecular signal, contributing to a mitotic DNA integrity checkpoint.

label.value: signal transduction involved in DNA integrity checkpoint

definition.value: A signal transduction process that contributes to a DNA integrity checkpoint.
